<script type="text/javascript">
var randomColor;
var randomLColor;
var penjodohanNomorAsli;
function inIframe () {
try {
return window.self !== window.top;
} catch (e) {
return true;
}
}
function shadeColor(color, percent) {
var R = parseInt(color.substring(1,3),16);
var G = parseInt(color.substring(3,5),16);
var B = parseInt(color.substring(5,7),16);
R = parseInt(R * (100 + percent) / 100);
G = parseInt(G * (100 + percent) / 100);
B = parseInt(B * (100 + percent) / 100);
R = (R<255)?R:255;
G = (G<255)?G:255;
B = (B<255)?B:255;
var RR = ((R.toString(16).length==1)?"0"+R.toString(16):R.toString(16));
var GG = ((G.toString(16).length==1)?"0"+G.toString(16):G.toString(16));
var BB = ((B.toString(16).length==1)?"0"+B.toString(16):B.toString(16));
return "#"+RR+GG+BB;
}
function randomLightColor() {
var letters = 'BCDEF'.split('');
var color = '#';
for (var i = 0; i < 6; i++ ) {
color += letters[Math.floor(Math.random() * letters.length)];
}
return color;
}
$(document).ready(function () {
$('body').on("click",".jawabulang", function () {
$(this).closest('.soal').find('connection').each(function(){
$(this).remove();
})
$(this).closest('.soal').find('td').each(function(){
$(this).css("background","none");
})
$(this).closest('.soal').find('.sradio').each(function(){
$(this).css("background","none");
})
$(this).closest('.soal').find('.dradio').each(function(){
$(this).css("background","none");
})
})
$('body').on("click",".sradio", function () {
randomColor = "#" + Math.floor(Math.random()*16777215).toString(16);
randomLColor = randomLightColor();
randomColor = "#" + Math.floor(Math.random()*16777215).toString(16);

$(this).css('background',randomLColor);
})
});

if ($('.rs1').length) {
$(this).css('background',"#2D46B9");

$(this).css('background',randomLColor);
})

$('#soal-body .soal').css("position", "relative");

$().connections({
from : ".rs1",
to : ".rd1",
within : $(this).closest('.soal'),
css : {
background: 'linear-gradient(to bottom right, transparent calc(50% - 3px), '+ randomColor +' calc(50% - 3px), '+ randomColor +' 50%, transparent 50%)'
}
});
let x = $(this).closest('.soal').find('connection').last();
x.width(x.width() + 15);
x.height(x.height() + 15);
} else {
$().connections({
from : ".rs1",
to : ".rd1",
within : $(this).closest('.soal'),
css : {
background: 'linear-gradient(to bottom left, transparent calc(50% - 3px), '+ randomColor +' calc(50% - 3px), '+ randomColor +' 50%, transparent 50%)'
}
});
let x = $(this).closest('.soal').find('connection').last();
x.width(x.width() + 15);
x.height(x.height() + 15);
let topInt = parseInt(x.css('top'));
console.log (topInt);
x.css("top",(topInt - 10) + "px");
}
$('.rs1').removeClass('rs1');
$('.rd1').removeClass('rd1');
}
});

<script>
String.prototype.replaceAll = function(search, replacement) {
var target = this;
return target.replace(new RegExp(search, 'g'), replacement);
};


jQuery(document).ready(function($) {

var nama_siswa2 = localStorage.getItem("siswa.namasiswa");
nama_siswa2 = nama_siswa2.replace("\\\\'", "'");

if (localStorage.getItem("data.finish") == 1) {
alert('Anda sudah selesai mengerjakan test ini');
window.location = 'http://103.196.153.71//';
exit();
}

$('#nama_siswa').text(localStorage.getItem("siswa.username"));
$('#nama_siswa2').text(nama_siswa2);
$('#localstorage').val(localStorage.getItem("data.localstorage"));

$('#mapel').val(localStorage.getItem("siswa.mapel"));
$('#userid').text(localStorage.getItem("siswa.username"));
$('#kodetest').val(localStorage.getItem("siswa.mapel"));
$.ajax({
url: 'http://103.196.153.71/wp-content/themes/unbk/images/foto/' + localStorage.getItem("siswa.username") + '.jpg',
type: 'HEAD',
error: function() {
console.log("Foto tidak ditemukan. Menggunakan Avatar Default");
$('#avatar img').prop({
src: 'http://103.196.153.71/wp-content/themes/unbk/images/avatar.png'
});
},
success: function() {
$('#avatar img').prop({
src: 'http://103.196.153.71/wp-content/themes/unbk/images/foto/' + localStorage.getItem("siswa.username") + '.jpg'
});
}
});

//LOAD SOAL JS PHP

var mapel = localStorage.getItem("siswa.mapel");
mapel = mapel.replaceAll(' ', '%20');

var soaljsphp = "http://103.196.153.71/wp-content/themes/unbk/js/soal.js.php?bv=13.7.12&shuffle=" + localStorage.getItem("mapel.shuffle") + "&mapel_dikerjakan=" + localStorage.getItem("mapel.dikerjakan") + "&alokasi=" + localStorage.getItem("mapel.alokasi") + "&waktu=" + localStorage.getItem("mapel.waktu") + "&namasiswa=" + localStorage.getItem("siswa.namasiswa").replaceAll(" ", "%20") + "&siswa=" + localStorage.getItem("siswa.username") + "&mapel=" + mapel + "&kodetest=" + localStorage.getItem("siswa.mapel").replaceAll(" ", "%20") + "&_=" + Date.now();
var soaljsphp2 = "http://103.196.153.71/wp-content/themes/unbk/archives/js/script.js?bv=13.7.12";
var soaljsphp0 = "http://103.196.153.71/wp-content/themes/unbk/archives/js/soal.js?bv=13.7.12";
$.ajaxSetup({
cache: true
});
console.log('Script 0 Loading : ' + soaljsphp0);
console.log('Script 1 Loading : ' + soaljsphp);
console.log('Script 2 Loading : ' + soaljsphp2);

$.getScript(soaljsphp0, function() {
console.log('Script 0 Loaded : ' + soaljsphp0);
$.getScript(soaljsphp, function() {
console.log('Script 1 Loaded : ' + soaljsphp);
$.getScript(soaljsphp2, function() {
console.log('Script 2 Loaded : ' + soaljsphp2);
})
});
})

$('body').addClass('logged-in');
$('body').addClass('soal-in');
});

<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">1</span> </p>
</td>
<td colspan="2" style="padding-left: 7px; padding-right: 7px; border-top: solid 0.5pt; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid 0.5pt; border-right: solid 0.5pt">
<p style="text-align: center"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt"><strong>Tourism Should give Benefit to Local People</strong><br />
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">What is the benefit of tourism for local people? Well, Tourism is now a huge contributor to the economies of most countries. Tourism industries can bring money, job vacancy and advancement especially to developing regions. However, this money often goes into the pockets of foreign investors, and the local people only get little benefit from it. Why?<br />
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">Multinational hotel chains don&#8217;t care about the surrounding nature when they build new hotels. This can cause many social, cultural and geographical problems. Moreover, some facts show that tourists tend to go, visit and spend their money in restaurants, bars and even luxury hotels of that multinational chain. They less go to restaurants, bars, hotels, shops owned by local people. This can prevent the local people&#8217;s business from becoming even larger.<br />
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">The other thing we must realize is that tours or excursions of tourism bring the negative effect on nature. It can disturb or destroy ecosystems and environments, and if it does, the local people will get the risk.<br />
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">From the facts above the local government should ensure that tourism can give benefits to the local people and it doesn&#8217;t destroy the nature.<br />
</span></p>
<p style="background: white">
 </p>
<p style="background: white"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">What is the similarity between paragraph two and three?<br />
</span></p>

<td style="padding-left: 7px; padding-right: 7px; border-top: none; border-left: solid 0.5pt; border-bottom: solid 0.5pt; border-right: solid 0.5pt">
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">4</span> </p>
</td>
<td colspan="2" style="padding-left: 7px; padding-right: 7px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid 0.5pt; border-right: solid 0.5pt">
<p style="text-align: justify"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">Once upon a time, there was a puppeteer named Geppetto. He really wanted a boy but his wife has been died for a long time ago. One day he had an idea. He wanted to make a puppet so he would never felt lonely again. He made a puppet all night without resting. In the morning, finally he finished his work. He named the puppet, Pinocchio. He played whole day with Pinocchio. However, he felt lonely again because Pinocchio couldn&#8217;t talk or walk by himself. In the middle of the night, Geppetto prayed to the God. He wish was Pinocchio became a real boy, human. He thought it on his mind in his dream.<br />
</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">In the morning, he surprised. Pinocchio was alive. He really was happy. He tough Pinocchio how to walk, how to speak, how to read etc. like a teacher. Pinocchio learned fast. He entered an elementary school. One day Pinocchio felt bored. So, he went home late. Geppetto worried about him. When Pinocchio came to home, Geppetto asked him. He said he was on school but he didn&#8217;t. Suddenly, Pinocchio&#8217;s nose grew longer. It meant that Pinocchio lied.<br />
</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">The next day, Pinocchio got caught by thieves. The thieves were the owner of circus. Pinocchio became a slave for the circus. He was famous because he was a talking puppet. Geppetto worried him. Pinocchio didn&#8217;t come home for 2 days. He found Pinocchio everywhere. When he discovered the sea, big wave smashed him. He was on whale&#8217;s stomach when he awoke. He couldn&#8217;t find the way out.<br />
</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">In different place, Pinocchio finally could get out from circus. He went to home but Geppetto wasn&#8217;t on there. He found Geppetto at sea. He had the same accident like Geppetto. He met Geppetto in whale&#8217;s stomach. They got out from its stomach by made a fire.They went home back together. In the end, they lived happy forever after.<br />
</span></p>
<p style="background: white">
 </p>
<p style="background: white"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">What is the story telling you about?<br />
</span></p>
</td>

<td style="padding-left: 7px; padding-right: 7px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid 0.5pt; border-right: solid 0.5pt">
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">The life of Pinocchio</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="padding-left: 7px; padding-right: 7px; border-top: none; border-left: solid 0.5pt; border-bottom: solid 0.5pt; border-right: solid 0.5pt">
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">5</span> </p>
</td>
<td colspan="2" style="padding-left: 7px; padding-right: 7px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid 0.5pt; border-right: solid 0.5pt">
<p style="text-align: justify"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">Once upon a time, there was a puppeteer named Geppetto. He really wanted a boy but his wife has been died for a long time ago. One day he had an idea. He wanted to make a puppet so he would never felt lonely again. He made a puppet all night without resting. In the morning, finally he finished his work. He named the puppet, Pinocchio. He played whole day with Pinocchio. However, he felt lonely again because Pinocchio couldn&#8217;t talk or walk by himself. In the middle of the night, Geppetto prayed to the God. He wish was Pinocchio became a real boy, human. He thought it on his mind in his dream.<br />
</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">In the morning, he surprised. Pinocchio was alive. He really was happy. He tough Pinocchio how to walk, how to speak, how to read etc. like a teacher. Pinocchio learned fast. He entered an elementary school. One day Pinocchio felt bored. So, he went home late. Geppetto worried about him. When Pinocchio came to home, Geppetto asked him. He said he was on school but he didn&#8217;t. Suddenly, Pinocchio&#8217;s nose grew longer. It meant that Pinocchio lied.<br />
</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">The next day, Pinocchio got caught by thieves. The thieves were the owner of circus. Pinocchio became a slave for the circus. He was famous because he was a talking puppet. Geppetto worried him. Pinocchio didn&#8217;t come home for 2 days. He found Pinocchio everywhere. When he discovered the sea, big wave smashed him. He was on whale&#8217;s stomach when he awoke. He couldn&#8217;t find the way out.<br />
</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">In different place, Pinocchio finally could get out from circus. He went to home but Geppetto wasn&#8217;t on there. He found Geppetto at sea. He had the same accident like Geppetto. He met Geppetto in whale&#8217;s stomach. They got out from its stomach by made a fire.They went home back together. In the end, they lived happy forever after.<br />
</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify">
 </p>
<p style="text-align: justify"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">What can you learn from the story?</span></p>

<td colspan="2" style="padding-left: 7px; padding-right: 7px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid 0.5pt; border-right: solid 0.5pt">
<p style="text-align: justify; background: white"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">Long, long ago, when the gods and goddesses used to mingle in the affairs of mortals, there was a small kingdom on the slope of Mount Wayang in West Java.  The King, named Sang Prabu, was a wise man.  He had an only daughter, called Princess Teja Nirmala, who was famous for her beauty but she was not married.  One day Sang Prabu made up his mind to settle the matter by a show of strength.<br />
</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify; background: white"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">After that, Prince of Blambangan, named Raden Begawan had won the competition.  Unfortunately, the wicked fairy, Princess Segara fell in love with Raden Begawan and used magic power to render him unconscious and he forgot his wedding.  When Sang Prabu was searching,<br />
</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify; background: white"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">Raden Begawan saw him and soon realized that he had been enchanted by the wicked fairy.  The fairy could not accept this, so she killed Raden Begawan.  When Princess Teja Nirmala heard this, she was very sad.  So a nice fairy took her to the Kahyangan.<br />
</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">Which one of the following statements is false about Sang Prabu?</span></p>

<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">9</span> </p>

<td colspan="2" style="padding-left: 7px; padding-right: 7px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid 0.5pt; border-right: solid 0.5pt">
<p style="text-align: justify; background: white"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">Long, long ago, when the gods and goddesses used to mingle in the affairs of mortals, there was a small kingdom on the slope of Mount Wayang in West Java.  The King, named Sang Prabu, was a wise man.  He had an only daughter, called Princess Teja Nirmala, who was famous for her beauty but she was not married.  One day Sang Prabu made up his mind to settle the matter by a show of strength.<br />
</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify; background: white"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">After that, Prince of Blambangan, named Raden Begawan had won the competition.  Unfortunately, the wicked fairy, Princess Segara fell in love with Raden Begawan and used magic power to render him unconscious and he forgot his wedding.  When Sang Prabu was searching,<br />
</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify; background: white"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">Raden Begawan saw him and soon realized that he had been enchanted by the wicked fairy.  The fairy could not accept this, so she killed Raden Begawan.  When Princess Teja Nirmala heard this, she was very sad.  So a nice fairy took her to the Kahyangan.<br />
</span></p>

<td colspan="2" style="padding-left: 7px; padding-right: 7px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid 0.5pt; border-right: solid 0.5pt">
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">After three months, the micro hydropower plant was finally completed. Finally, the houses where they lived were in joy at night. Those who previously doubted the value of hard work, cooperation, and care for environment then joined in cheers. Villagers were then more enthusiastic about protecting the forest and the surrounding environment to keep the water supplies remaining available. Nayau smiled broadly and was proud of his friends.&#8221; The beauty of Gurung Mali village will stay forever and people will be more prosperous since they are more productive now,&#8221; Nayau whispered &#8220;Togetherness can break through limitations&#8221;<br />

<p style="margin-left: 61pt"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt"><strong>Sri</strong>     : &#8220;Well, let me start from the reason why I decided to start my online shop. When I was a little girl back then, I remember saving my pocket money by placing it in a special rooster piggy bank, the silver rupiah coins collected into a pile full of coins. <td style="padding-left: 7px; padding-right: 7px; border-top: none; border-left: solid 0.5pt; border-bottom: solid 0.5pt; border-right: solid 0.5pt">
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">21</span> </p>
</td>
<td colspan="2" style="padding-left: 7px; padding-right: 7px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid 0.5pt; border-right: solid 0.5pt">
<p style="text-align: center; margin-left: 28pt"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt"><strong>The Use of E-Money<br />
</strong></span></p>
<p style="text-align: center; margin-left: 28pt">
 </p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">In recent years, e-money has become increasingly popular as an alternative to physical cash. This shift has raised important discussions about the advantages and disadvantages of using e-money in everyday transactions.<br />
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">On one hand, supporters of e-money argue that it is far more convenient than carrying physical cash. With e-money, consumers can make quick and easy payments using smartphones or cards without the need to carry bulky wallets. Additionally, e-money provides detailed transaction histories, which helps users keep track of their spending more effectively. This is particularly beneficial in a digital era where budgeting is essential.<br />
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">On the other hand, critics of e-money express concerns about security and spending habits. One common worry is the risk of cyberattacks and fraud, as e-money is stored electronically and can be vulnerable to hacking or theft. Additionally, some people fear that the ease of using e-money may lead to impulsive spending since it doesn&#8217;t feel as tangible as handing over cash. They argue that the &#8220;pain of paying&#8221; is less apparent, which could lead to overspending.<br />
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">In conclusion, while e-money offers convenience and practicality, it also comes with risks that should not be ignored. Whether one chooses to use e-money or stick to physical cash depends on individual preferences and how they manage their finances. As the world continues to shift towards cashless transactions, this debate is likely to become even more relevant in the future.<br />
</span></p>
<p>
 </p>
<p>
 </p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">What is one advantage of using e-money according to supporters?<br />
</span></p>

</td>
<td style="padding-left: 7px; padding-right: 7px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid 0.5pt; border-right: solid 0.5pt">
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">It protects users from overspending.</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="padding-left: 7px; padding-right: 7px; border-top: none; border-left: solid 0.5pt; border-bottom: solid 0.5pt; border-right: solid 0.5pt">
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">22</span> </p>
</td>
<td colspan="2" style="padding-left: 7px; padding-right: 7px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid 0.5pt; border-right: solid 0.5pt">
<p style="text-align: center; margin-left: 28pt"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt"><strong>The Use of E-Money<br />
</strong></span></p>
<p style="text-align: center; margin-left: 28pt">
 </p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">In recent years, e-money has become increasingly popular as an alternative to physical cash. This shift has raised important discussions about the advantages and disadvantages of using e-money in everyday transactions.<br />
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">On one hand, supporters of e-money argue that it is far more convenient than carrying physical cash. With e-money, consumers can make quick and easy payments using smartphones or cards without the need to carry bulky wallets. Additionally, e-money provides detailed transaction histories, which helps users keep track of their spending more effectively. This is particularly beneficial in a digital era where budgeting is essential.<br />
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">On the other hand, critics of e-money express concerns about security and spending habits. One common worry is the risk of cyberattacks and fraud, as e-money is stored electronically and can be vulnerable to hacking or theft. Additionally, some people fear that the ease of using e-money may lead to impulsive spending since it doesn&#8217;t feel as tangible as handing over cash. They argue that the &#8220;pain of paying&#8221; is less apparent, which could lead to overspending.<br />
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">In conclusion, while e-money offers convenience and practicality, it also comes with risks that should not be ignored. Whether one chooses to use e-money or stick to physical cash depends on individual preferences and how they manage their finances. As the world continues to shift towards cashless transactions, this debate is likely to become even more relevant in the future.<br />
</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify">
 </p>
<p style="text-align: justify"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">What is a major concern of critics regarding e-money?</span></p>

<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">E-money should only be used for small transactions.</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="padding-left: 7px; padding-right: 7px; border-top: none; border-left: solid 0.5pt; border-bottom: solid 0.5pt; border-right: solid 0.5pt">
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">26</span> </p>
</td>
<td colspan="2" style="padding-left: 7px; padding-right: 7px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid 0.5pt; border-right: solid 0.5pt">
<p style="text-align: center; margin-left: 28pt"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt"><strong>E-Money as a Lifestyle<br />
</strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">E-money is rapidly becoming a part of modern life, transforming the way people handle their financial transactions. As digital technology becomes more integrated into daily routines, e-money is no longer just an option for tech-savvy individuals but a lifestyle choice for many. This shift has sparked debates about its impact on how people manage their money and whether it is a positive development.<br />
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt"><strong>Proponents</strong> of e-money argue that it simplifies life by allowing faster, more convenient payments. With e-money, there is no need to carry physical cash or worry about having the exact change. Everything can be done with the tap of a card or smartphone. In this way, e-money has created a more seamless experience for people who want efficiency in their daily transactions.<br />
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">Moreover, e-money provides added benefits, such as easier access to online shopping and global markets. Consumers can shop without geographical limitations, paying for goods and services from anywhere in the world. E-money users often enjoy discounts and rewards, which make it an attractive option for those who want more value from their spending.<br />
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt"><strong>On the other hand</strong>, critics express concerns about the reliance on digital systems for transactions. One major issue is security. Digital transactions are vulnerable to hacking, identity theft, and other cybercrimes. People worry that as e-money becomes more embedded in society, they could face risks like unauthorized transactions or losing access to their accounts during system outages.<br />
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">Another concern is that e-money can promote overspending. Since e-money transactions do not involve physically handing over cash, some users may lose track of their spending. The ease of electronic payments could lead to impulsive buying and financial difficulties for people who are not disciplined in managing their finances.<br />
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">In conclusion, while e-money offers undeniable convenience and opens up a world of new opportunities, it also presents risks that users must consider. Whether e-money is a positive lifestyle change depends on how individuals balance its benefits with its potential downsides.<br />
</span></p>

<td style="padding-left: 7px; padding-right: 7px; border-top: none; border-left: solid 0.5pt; border-bottom: solid 0.5pt; border-right: solid 0.5pt"> </td>
<td style="padding-left: 7px; padding-right: 7px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid 0.5pt; border-right: solid 0.5pt">
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">C</span> </p>

</td>

<td style="padding-left: 7px; padding-right: 7px; border-top: none; border-left: solid 0.5pt; border-bottom: solid 0.5pt; border-right: solid 0.5pt"> </td>
<td style="padding-left: 7px; padding-right: 7px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid 0.5pt; border-right: solid 0.5pt">
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">D</span> </p>

</td>

<td style="padding-left: 7px; padding-right: 7px; border-top: none; border-left: solid 0.5pt; border-bottom: solid 0.5pt; border-right: solid 0.5pt">
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">30</span> </p>
</td>
<td colspan="2" style="padding-left: 7px; padding-right: 7px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid 0.5pt; border-right: solid 0.5pt">
<p style="text-align: center; margin-left: 28pt"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt"><strong>E-Money as a Lifestyle<br />
</strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">E-money is rapidly becoming a part of modern life, transforming the way people handle their financial transactions. As digital technology becomes more integrated into daily routines, e-money is no longer just an option for tech-savvy individuals but a lifestyle choice for many. This shift has sparked debates about its impact on how people manage their money and whether it is a positive development.<br />
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt"><strong>Proponents</strong> of e-money argue that it simplifies life by allowing faster, more convenient payments. With e-money, there is no need to carry physical cash or worry about having the exact change. Everything can be done with the tap of a card or smartphone. In this way, e-money has created a more seamless experience for people who want efficiency in their daily transactions.<br />
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">Moreover, e-money provides added benefits, such as easier access to online shopping and global markets. Consumers can shop without geographical limitations, paying for goods and services from anywhere in the world. E-money users often enjoy discounts and rewards, which make it an attractive option for those who want more value from their spending.<br />
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt"><strong>On the other hand</strong>, critics express concerns about the reliance on digital systems for transactions. One major issue is security. Digital transactions are vulnerable to hacking, identity theft, and other cybercrimes. People worry that as e-money becomes more embedded in society, they could face risks like unauthorized transactions or losing access to their accounts during system outages.<br />
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">Another concern is that e-money can promote overspending. Since e-money transactions do not involve physically handing over cash, some users may lose track of their spending. The ease of electronic payments could lead to impulsive buying and financial difficulties for people who are not disciplined in managing their finances.<br />
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">In conclusion, while e-money offers undeniable convenience and opens up a world of new opportunities, it also presents risks that users must consider. Whether e-money is a positive lifestyle change depends on how individuals balance its benefits with its potential downsides.<br />
</span></p>
<p>
 </p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">Which of the following is a <strong>concern</strong> raised about e-money?</span></p>

<p style="text-align: center"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt"><strong>Kilion and His Bright Amdui Village<br />
</strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">One day, in a dark remote village of East Indonesia, named Amdui, an old man, named Kilion Manggara, stayed in his dim light house. He wondered about his village which had been dark for many years. Amdui village had always relied on generators and outboard lamps for lightning at night.<br />
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">When he was a young elementary school teacher, the dim light helped him do the teacher&#8217;s work at home. Time passed but nothing had changed since then. As he got older and older, the light was not much to help him read all of his favorite books during the night. Yet, he was persistent to stay on track.<br />
</span></p>

<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">PILIHAN GANDA KOMPLEKS<br />

<p style="text-align: center; margin-left: 28pt"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt"><strong>Transforming Indonesia&#8217;s Sumba into an Iconic Green Energy Island<br />
</strong></span></p>
<p style="text-align: center; margin-left: 36pt">
 </p>
<p style="background: white"><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=1" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">The island of Sumba in Eastern Indonesia </span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=4" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">is culturally distinct from the rest of </span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=6" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">the country with unique burial </span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=8" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">traditions, </span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=9" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">animist religions and its own unique </span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=11" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">language. </span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=12" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">But it shares many of the same problems </span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=15" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">as other isolated regions,</span></a><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt"> p<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=17" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">overty, high infant mortality, and </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=20" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">diseases like malaria common. </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=24" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">Access to power for the 650 000 </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=26" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">islanders </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=27" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">is a huge problem. Nearly half have no </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=30" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">access to electricity </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=32" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">and use kerosene and wood fires for </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=34" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">lighting and cooking. </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=36" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">It&#8217;s expensive unsafe and unhealthy. </a><br />
</span></p>
<p style="background: white"><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=40" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">Meanwhile the island has an abundance of </span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=42" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">renewable energy </span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=44" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">with plentiful solar and biomass </span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=46" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">resources </span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=47" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">and significant potential for hydro </span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=49" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">power and wind. </span></a><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">To harness this green energy for Sumba T<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=53" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">he Dutch NGO Hivos began working with </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=56" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">the government. </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=57" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">They set an ambitious goal to extend </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=60" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">electricity to the vast majority of </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=62" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">symbols population </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=64" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">using 100 percent renewable energy. </a><br />
</span></p>
<p style="background: white"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">This initiative to turn Sumba into an iconic island of clean energy has since attracted <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=92" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">has since attracted additional support </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=94" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">from other development partners, </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=96" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">the private sector, and most recently the </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=98" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">ADB. Progress has already been made in </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=101" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">rolling out renewable energy. </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=103" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">The village of <em>Wee Libo</em> benefits from </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=106" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">a government-sponsored small-scale </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=108" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">solar project. It brings power to 36 </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=111" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">houses for a small monthly fee, </a>m<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=114" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">uch lower than the household kerosene </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=116" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">bill. </a><br />
</span></p>
<p style="background: white"><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=117" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">For village headman, Lede Dauga, having </span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=120" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">electricity at home </span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=121" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">has changed his life.</span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=136" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt"> And for the rest of the village, it means </span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=137" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">the chance to work and study after dark </span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=140" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">and access to things like television for the first time</span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=143" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">.</span></a><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt"><br />
</span></p>
<p style="background: white"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">ADB joined the initiative in 2013 with a technical assistance grant worth one million dollars. It&#8217;s aimed at scaling up renewable energy access in Sumba and in other areas of Eastern Indonesia. This was later increased to two million dollars with a grant from the government of Norway.<br />
</span></p>
<p style="background: white"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">ADB&#8217;s involvement can help leverage this model across other geographies within Indonesia and outside of Indonesia by supporting the overall development of the program and the subsequent implementation that can provide a model that can be replicated elsewhere.<br />
</span></p>
<p style="background: white"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">This ambitious energy experiment on Somber is important if it&#8217;s a success on the island. It could enable Indonesia to widen cost-effective energy access across many other poor isolated communities.<br />
</span></p>
<p style="background: white">
 </p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">Source : Sumba<br />
</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">Hivos is an international development organization that helps build social movements that strive for just, inclusive and sustainable societies.<br />
</span></p>

<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">PILIHAN GANDA KOMPLEKS<br />
</span></p>
<p style="text-align: center; margin-left: 28pt"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt"><strong>Transforming Indonesia&#8217;s Sumba into an Iconic Green Energy Island<br />
</strong></span></p>
<p style="text-align: center; margin-left: 36pt">
 </p>
<p style="background: white"><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=1" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">The island of Sumba in Eastern Indonesia </span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=4" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">is culturally distinct from the rest of </span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=6" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">the country with unique burial </span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=8" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">traditions, </span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=9" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">animist religions and its own unique </span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=11" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">language. </span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=12" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">But it shares many of the same problems </span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=15" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">as other isolated regions,</span></a><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt"> p<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=17" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">overty, high infant mortality, and </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=20" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">diseases like malaria common. </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=24" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">Access to power for the 650 000 </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=26" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">islanders </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=27" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">is a huge problem. Nearly half have no </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=30" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">access to electricity </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=32" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">and use kerosene and wood fires for </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=34" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">lighting and cooking. </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=36" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">It&#8217;s expensive unsafe and unhealthy. </a><br />
</span></p>
<p style="background: white"><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=40" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">Meanwhile the island has an abundance of </span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=42" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">renewable energy </span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=44" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">with plentiful solar and biomass </span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=46" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">resources </span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=47" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">and significant potential for hydro </span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=49" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">power and wind. </span></a><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">To harness this green energy for Sumba T<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=53" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">he Dutch NGO Hivos began working with </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=56" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">the government. </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=57" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">They set an ambitious goal to extend </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=60" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">electricity to the vast majority of </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=62" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">symbols population </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=64" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">using 100 percent renewable energy. </a><br />
</span></p>
<p style="background: white"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">This initiative to turn Sumba into an iconic island of clean energy has since attracted <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=92" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">has since attracted additional support </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=94" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">from other development partners, </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=96" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">the private sector, and most recently the </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=98" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">ADB. Progress has already been made in </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=101" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">rolling out renewable energy. </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=103" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">The village of <em>Wee Libo</em> benefits from </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=106" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">a government-sponsored small-scale </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=108" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">solar project. It brings power to 36 </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=111" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">houses for a small monthly fee, </a>m<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=114" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">uch lower than the household kerosene </a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=116" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video">bill. </a><br />
</span></p>
<p style="background: white"><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=117" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">For village headman, Lede Dauga, having </span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=120" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">electricity at home </span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=121" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">has changed his life.</span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=136" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt"> And for the rest of the village, it means </span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=137" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">the chance to work and study after dark </span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=140" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">and access to things like television for the first time</span></a><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E-TPtCWsj4s&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;t=143" target="_blank" title="Click to see this sentence in the video"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">.</span></a><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt"><br />
</span></p>
<p style="background: white"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">ADB joined the initiative in 2013 with a technical assistance grant worth one million dollars. It&#8217;s aimed at scaling up renewable energy access in Sumba and in other areas of Eastern Indonesia. This was later increased to two million dollars with a grant from the government of Norway.<br />
</span></p>
<p style="background: white"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">ADB&#8217;s involvement can help leverage this model across other geographies within Indonesia and outside of Indonesia by supporting the overall development of the program and the subsequent implementation that can provide a model that can be replicated elsewhere.<br />
</span></p>
<p style="background: white"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">This ambitious energy experiment on Somber is important if it&#8217;s a success on the island. It could enable Indonesia to widen cost-effective energy access across many other poor isolated communities.<br />
</span></p>
<p style="background: white">
 </p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">Source : Sumba<br />
</span></p>

</span></p>

</span></p>
<p style="background: white"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">ADB joined the initiative in 2013 with a technical assistance grant worth one million dollars. It&#8217;s aimed at scaling up renewable energy access in Sumba and in other areas of Eastern Indonesia. This was later increased to two million dollars with a grant from the government of Norway.<br />
</span></p>
<p style="background: white"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">ADB&#8217;s involvement can help leverage this model across other geographies within Indonesia and outside of Indonesia by supporting the overall development of the program and the subsequent implementation that can provide a model that can be replicated elsewhere.<br />
</span></p>
<p style="background: white"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">This ambitious energy experiment on Somber is important if it&#8217;s a success on the island. It could enable Indonesia to widen cost-effective energy access across many other poor isolated communities.<br />
</span></p>

<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt"><strong>TRUE AND FALSE QUESTIONS<br />
</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin-left: 21pt">
 </p>
<p style="text-align: center; margin-left: 28pt"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt"><strong>The Use of E-Money<br />
</strong></span></p>
<p style="text-align: center; margin-left: 28pt">
 </p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">In recent years, e-money has become increasingly popular as an alternative to physical cash. This shift has raised important discussions about the advantages and disadvantages of using e-money in everyday transactions.<br />
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">On one hand, supporters of e-money argue that it is far more convenient than carrying physical cash. With e-money, consumers can make quick and easy payments using smartphones or cards without the need to carry bulky wallets. Additionally, e-money provides detailed transaction histories, which helps users keep track of their spending more effectively. This is particularly beneficial in a digital era where budgeting is essential.<br />
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">On the other hand, critics of e-money express concerns about security and spending habits. One common worry is the risk of cyberattacks and fraud, as e-money is stored electronically and can be vulnerable to hacking or theft. Additionally, some people fear that the ease of using e-money may lead to impulsive spending since it doesn&#8217;t feel as tangible as handing over cash. They argue that the &#8220;pain of paying&#8221; is less apparent, which could lead to overspending.<br />
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">In conclusion, while e-money offers convenience and practicality, it also comes with risks that should not be ignored. Whether one chooses to use e-money or stick to physical cash depends on individual preferences and how they manage their finances. As the world continues to shift towards cashless transactions, this debate is likely to become even more relevant in the future.<br />
</span></p>

<td colspan="2" style="padding-left: 7px; padding-right: 7px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid 0.5pt; border-right: solid 0.5pt">
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt"><strong>TRUE AND FALSE QUESTIONS<br />
</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin-left: 21pt">
 </p>
<p style="text-align: center; margin-left: 28pt"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt"><strong>The Use of E-Money<br />
</strong></span></p>
<p style="text-align: center; margin-left: 28pt">
 </p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">In recent years, e-money has become increasingly popular as an alternative to physical cash. This shift has raised important discussions about the advantages and disadvantages of using e-money in everyday transactions.<br />
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">On one hand, supporters of e-money argue that it is far more convenient than carrying physical cash. With e-money, consumers can make quick and easy payments using smartphones or cards without the need to carry bulky wallets. Additionally, e-money provides detailed transaction histories, which helps users keep track of their spending more effectively. This is particularly beneficial in a digital era where budgeting is essential.<br />
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">On the other hand, critics of e-money express concerns about security and spending habits. One common worry is the risk of cyberattacks and fraud, as e-money is stored electronically and can be vulnerable to hacking or theft. Additionally, some people fear that the ease of using e-money may lead to impulsive spending since it doesn&#8217;t feel as tangible as handing over cash. They argue that the &#8220;pain of paying&#8221; is less apparent, which could lead to overspending.<br />
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">In conclusion, while e-money offers convenience and practicality, it also comes with risks that should not be ignored. Whether one chooses to use e-money or stick to physical cash depends on individual preferences and how they manage their finances. As the world continues to shift towards cashless transactions, this debate is likely to become even more relevant in the future.<br />
</span></p>
<p>
 </p>

</span></p>

<td style="padding-left: 7px; padding-right: 7px; border-top: none; border-left: solid 0.5pt; border-bottom: solid 0.5pt; border-right: solid 0.5pt">
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">38</span></p>
</td>
<td colspan="2" style="padding-left: 7px; padding-right: 7px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid 0.5pt; border-right: solid 0.5pt">
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt"><strong>TRUE AND FALSE QUESTIONS<br />
</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin-left: 21pt">
 </p>
<p style="text-align: center; margin-left: 28pt"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt"><strong>The Use of E-Money<br />
</strong></span></p>
<p style="text-align: center; margin-left: 28pt">
 </p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">In recent years, e-money has become increasingly popular as an alternative to physical cash. This shift has raised important discussions about the advantages and disadvantages of using e-money in everyday transactions.<br />
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">On one hand, supporters of e-money argue that it is far more convenient than carrying physical cash. With e-money, consumers can make quick and easy payments using smartphones or cards without the need to carry bulky wallets. Additionally, e-money provides detailed transaction histories, which helps users keep track of their spending more effectively. This is particularly beneficial in a digital era where budgeting is essential.<br />
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">On the other hand, critics of e-money express concerns about security and spending habits. One common worry is the risk of cyberattacks and fraud, as e-money is stored electronically and can be vulnerable to hacking or theft. Additionally, some people fear that the ease of using e-money may lead to impulsive spending since it doesn&#8217;t feel as tangible as handing over cash. They argue that the &#8220;pain of paying&#8221; is less apparent, which could lead to overspending.<br />
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">In conclusion, while e-money offers convenience and practicality, it also comes with risks that should not be ignored. Whether one chooses to use e-money or stick to physical cash depends on individual preferences and how they manage their finances. As the world continues to shift towards cashless transactions, this debate is likely to become even more relevant in the future.<br />
</span></p>
<p>
 </p>

<td style="padding-left: 7px; padding-right: 7px; border-top: none; border-left: solid 0.5pt; border-bottom: solid 0.5pt; border-right: solid 0.5pt">
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">39</span></p>
</td>
<td colspan="2" style="padding-left: 7px; padding-right: 7px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid 0.5pt; border-right: solid 0.5pt">
<p style="text-align: justify"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt"><strong>TRUE AND FALSE QUESTIONS<br />
</strong></span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify">
 </p>
<p style="text-align: justify"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">One night, in the village of Gurung Mali in Sintang district of West Kalimantan, the night was colder and darker. There was no light at all. The enchanting beauty of Gurung Mali village during the day felt short and the night was very long. People couldn&#8217;t do anything other than go to bed, including a man named Nayau. Nayau often <span style="text-decoration:underline">contemplated</span> what he could do so that the beauty of his village could be seen even longer. This would make people be able to do more activities at night without any limitation.<br />
</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">&#8220;If we don&#8217;t try to change our condition, who else will change it for us?&#8221; Nayau said quietly. &#8220;We can&#8217;t just stand still, waiting for the electricity to come from the government and we don&#8217;t know when it will come,&#8221; Nayau added.<br />
</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">On the next day, they came to the materials shop to discuss the matter. After a few bargaining and such they made an agreement. They had a deal. Nayau and several supportive friends such as Apoi, Sinko, Hisako, Noh, Dasen, Supardi, Mio, Nino and several other women began working together to build a dam and a mill house along with the water cannel in the form of a ditch that reached 200 meters in length and 40 cm in depth. They worked collectively, piled sandbags for the dam, covered the mill house with tarpaulin and covered the generator with zinc. Everything was done manually. Every day, their profusely sweat was not felt as a barrier to their passions to change the condition of their village. They were eager to make their village enlightened and eliminate the limitations of their activities at night.<br />
</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">After three months, the micro hydropower plant was finally completed. Finally, the houses where they lived were in joy at night. Those who previously doubted the value of hard work, cooperation, and care for environment then joined in cheers. Villagers were then more enthusiastic about protecting the forest and the surrounding environment to keep the water supplies remaining available. Nayau smiled broadly and was proud of his friends.&#8221; The beauty of Gurung Mali village will stay forever and people will be more prosperous since they are more productive now,&#8221; Nayau whispered &#8220;Togetherness can break through limitations&#8221;<br />
</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify">
 </p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt"><span style="background-color:white">Decide whether the following statements are <strong>True</strong> or <strong>False</strong> ba</span>sed on the text above<br />
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">How was the ending of the story?<br />

</td>
<td colspan="2" style="padding-left: 7px; padding-right: 7px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid 0.5pt; border-right: solid 0.5pt">
<p style="text-align: justify"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt"><strong>TRUE AND FALSE QUESTIONS<br />
</strong></span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify">
 </p>
<p style="text-align: justify"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">One night, in the village of Gurung Mali in Sintang district of West Kalimantan, the night was colder and darker. There was no light at all. The enchanting beauty of Gurung Mali village during the day felt short and the night was very long. People couldn&#8217;t do anything other than go to bed, including a man named Nayau. Nayau often <span style="text-decoration:underline">contemplated</span> what he could do so that the beauty of his village could be seen even longer. This would make people be able to do more activities at night without any limitation.<br />
</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">&#8220;If we don&#8217;t try to change our condition, who else will change it for us?&#8221; Nayau said quietly. &#8220;We can&#8217;t just stand still, waiting for the electricity to come from the government and we don&#8217;t know when it will come,&#8221; Nayau added.<br />
</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">On the next day, they came to the materials shop to discuss the matter. After a few bargaining and such they made an agreement. They had a deal. Nayau and several supportive friends such as Apoi, Sinko, Hisako, Noh, Dasen, Supardi, Mio, Nino and several other women began working together to build a dam and a mill house along with the water cannel in the form of a ditch that reached 200 meters in length and 40 cm in depth. They worked collectively, piled sandbags for the dam, covered the mill house with tarpaulin and covered the generator with zinc. Everything was done manually. Every day, their profusely sweat was not felt as a barrier to their passions to change the condition of their village. They were eager to make their village enlightened and eliminate the limitations of their activities at night.<br />
</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify"><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">After three months, the micro hydropower plant was finally completed. Finally, the houses where they lived were in joy at night. Those who previously doubted the value of hard work, cooperation, and care for environment then joined in cheers. Villagers were then more enthusiastic about protecting the forest and the surrounding environment to keep the water supplies remaining available. Nayau smiled broadly and was proud of his friends.&#8221; The beauty of Gurung Mali village will stay forever and people will be more prosperous since they are more productive now,&#8221; Nayau whispered &#8220;Togetherness can break through limitations&#8221;<br />
</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify">
 </p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt"><span style="background-color:white">Decide whether the following statements are <strong>True</strong> or <strong>False</strong> ba</span>sed on the text above<br />
</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family:Arial Narrow; font-size:14pt">How did the villagers&#8217; attitude toward the environment change after the project?<br />
</span></p>
<p>
 </p>

<script>
var elem = document.documentElement;

/* Function to open fullscreen mode */
function openFullscreen() {
if (elem.requestFullscreen) {
elem.requestFullscreen();
} else if (elem.mozRequestFullScreen) {
/* Firefox */
elem.mozRequestFullScreen();
} else if (elem.webkitRequestFullscreen) {
/* Chrome, Safari & Opera */
elem.webkitRequestFullscreen();
} else if (elem.msRequestFullscreen) {
/* IE/Edge */
elem = window.top.document.body; //To break out of frame in IE
elem.msRequestFullscreen();
}
}
swal({
title: 'Informasi',
html: 'Mode Full Screen diaktifkan. pastikan tidak menutup browser. Mohon kerjakan soal ujian dengan jujur.',

// showCancelButton: true,
confirmButtonColor: '#3085d6',
cancelButtonColor: '#d33',
confirmButtonText: 'Mulai Ujian',
type: "info",
allowEscapeKey: false,
allowOutsideClick: false
}).then((result) => {
if (result.value) {
openFullscreen();
}
})

if (document.addEventListener) {
document.addEventListener('fullscreenchange', exitHandler, false);
document.addEventListener('mozfullscreenchange', exitHandler, false);
document.addEventListener('MSFullscreenChange', exitHandler, false);
document.addEventListener('webkitfullscreenchange', exitHandler, false);
}

function exitHandler() {
if (document.webkitIsFullScreen === false) {
var
closeInSeconds = 1,
displayText = "Ujian akan dilogout dalam #1 detik.",
timer;


timer = setInterval(function() {
closeInSeconds--;
if (closeInSeconds < 0) {
clearInterval(timer);
window.location = "http://103.196.153.71//";
}
$('.swal2-content').text(displayText.replace(/#1/, closeInSeconds));
}, 1000);
swal({
title: "Pelanggaran!",
text: displayText.replace(/#1/, closeInSeconds),
timer: closeInSeconds * 1000,
confirmButtonText: 'Lanjut Ujian',
type: "error",
allowEscapeKey: false,
allowOutsideClick: false
}).then((result) => {
if (result.value) {
clearInterval(timer);
openFullscreen();
}
})
} else if (document.mozFullScreen === false) {
console.log('bbbbbb')
} else if (document.msFullscreenElement === false) {
console.log('cccccc')
}
}

function selesai() {
var jawaban = [];
$('.option.checked').each(function(index, el) {
jawaban[$(this).attr('data-nomor-asli')] = $(this).attr('data-option-asli');
});
$('.options.checklist .option:not(.checked)').each(function() {
jawaban[$(this).attr('data-nomor-asli')] = "-" + $(this).attr('data-option-asli');
})
$('textarea.essay').each(function(index, el) {
jawaban[$(this).attr('data-nomor-asli')] = $(this).val() + ' ';
});
$('select.soallist').each(function(index, el) {
jawaban[$(this).attr('data-nomor-asli')] = $(this).val() + ' ';
});
kumpuljawaban(jawaban, 0);
}
